metadata.name: Metropolis IX #9
metadata.description:
We divide spaces into smaller spaces which we conquer and live in our solitude. We call that Metropolis.

Started this piece as a rule based generative art. Simply the algorithm takes a rectangle and throws 2 random points inside it within defined x and y distances. Then using those 2 points, algorithm draws another rectangle and assigns letters to the corners of rectangle "A,B,C,D" starting from top left corner in clockwise direction. Then it starts to draw cells from inner rectangle's corner A to parent's corner A and goes on. Once 4 cells are created, it creates 4 more cells in between other cells, thus dividing a rectangle into 9 pieces. This is where "IX" comes from. Depending on the cell properties; algorithm assigns circles, triangles, lines and points to cells creating a city scape when certain parameters are given to the division algorithm.

There are 18 possible outcomes:
"Hazy Day" 13% probability (half of this style will come with slightly more color transition)
"Hazy Night" 10% probability
"Crystal Day" 11% probability
"Crystal Night" 5% probability
"Mondrian Day"  3% probability
"Mondrian Night" 3% probability
"Bauhaus Day" 3% probability
"Bauhaus Night" 3% probability
"1 Chroma Day" 4% probability (Multiple values of a single hue on a monochrome gradient)
"Mondrian Crystal Day" 3% probability
"Mondrian Crystal Night" 3% probability
"Monochrome Day" 3% probability 
"Monochrome Night" 4% probability 
"Vibrant Day" 12% probability
"Vibrant Night" 9% probability
"Rainbow Day' 5% probability
"Rainbow Night' 3% probability
"Chaotic Day"   3% probability (which takes pretty random parameters and 25% of this outcome has probability of creating very first coloring style of the project, see console for the hidden feature)




Press "1" to download 1000px height PNG
Press "2" to download 2000px height PNG
Press "3" to download 3000px height PNG
Press "4" to download 4000px height PNG
Press "5" to download 5000px height PNG
Press "6" to download 6000px height PNG
Press "7" to download 7000px height PNG
Press "8" to download 8000px height PNG
Press "9" to download 12000px height PNG
Press "m' to download 900x1600px PNG for mobile wallpaper

Use CTRL+SHIFT+C or CMD+SHIFT+C to open console for hidden features

Created from scratch with p5.js 
Murat Atimtay 2022 | @atimtay | www.muratatimtay.com

metadata.name: Fire Card #199
metadata.description:
Fire Cards is a series of generative artworks inspired by 19th-century Japanese fireworks catalogues. The images in these catalogues didn't so much focus on realism, but on the visual associations of the pyrotechnic effects instead. Using a restricted color palette and relatively simple shapes, this resulted in vibrant, graphical posters that sparked your own imagination more than anything else.

In Fire Cards, the abstract, static images are transformed back into lively, dynamic worlds again, each with their own distinctive, centuries-old aesthetics. Using a custom animation and 2D render system, the algorithmically generated worlds slowly build up and show a magical fireworks performance.

Fire Cards are tiny, personal and unique shows of wonder.

metadata.name: Different Intersections - Iteration 4 #13
metadata.description:
This is the culmination of a series of iterations

____ - Iteration 1
____ - Iteration 2
____ - Iteration 3

The iterations were released under the pseudonym Extracurricular Activities.

The algorithmic theme of the iterations was extensive usage of boolean operations (intersection and difference) on polygons to derive interesting composite shapes.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

metadata.name: Geoetris #152
metadata.description:
In 'Geoetris', the random mixture of simple geometric forms and vibrant colour palettes converge towards an artistic manifestation of geometric abstraction.


The collection is limited to 161 works of art, the first three digits of the golden ratio, a number often encountered when taking the ratios of distances in geometric figures.

-----

Press 's' to save a high resolution PNG at 10000 x 10000 px.
Press 'e' to save the current canvas view.

-----

Features:

Palette: dark1, dark2, dark3, vrolik1, vrolik2, retro1, retro2, origami, magma, jungle, lava, tuscany
Background: derived from the palette
Partitions: partitions,
Noisy: true, false


-----

Artwork by @cristianrohr.

Made with P5js and <3.

metadata.name: Sprocket Factory #272
metadata.description:
Just an ordinary scene from a typical day, working as a Sprocket Factory engineer. Inspiration for this work is drawn from the composable nature of blockchain smart contracts and the flow of value between networks of autonomous machines and free-willed individuals.

"A Doodle, Ringer, and Fidenza walk into a Space Bar..."

- Press "P" to export an PNG raster image (10k resolution.)
- Press "S" to export an SVG vector.

metadata.name: Rhythms #243
metadata.description:
"Routines, patterns, cadence.
Events, turns, chaos.
Predictable lives,
split-second dramas."

This project is inspired by the delicate balance between daily habits and life-turning points.
There's structure in the flow. There's awe in the silence.

"Rhythms" invites you to reflect on the beautiful complexity that fills our vital experience, on the millions of tiny details that bring texture to our journey causing balance or disruption.

-

Key Features:
- 12 color palettes: Determines colors used on the artwork
- 3 Orientation modes (square, portrait, landscape): Portrait and landscape are rare
- 6 Alignment Types: Determines lines' distribution pattern

Secondary features provide additional variation.

Enter live mode and press "s" to download high resolution image ( 5940x5940 px ).

-

50% of secondary market royalties go to minters.
Coded in p5js, with love.

metadata.name: Toccata #66
metadata.description:
Toccata is a piece about decay, about the impermanent. The emergence over time or, rather, progression of entropy is a key characteristic of our universe. Everything evolves to nothing. We as mortal beings have sometimes trouble reconciling with this idea. Humans have sought immortality for millennia, be it through ancient potions or modern medicine, be it from leaving a legacy that we feel will stand the test of time. It will, only to decay later than us.

Toccata is a piece about change. Change lies at the heart of human cognition and human nature. Our thoughts and our emotions happen over time, and are a function of the change that is both around us and at the very core of our selves. Change comes in nature in cycles. Seasons of growth, seasons of ripe fruits of life, seasons of decay, of death, rebirth.

Toccata is music. We find music to convey some of the deepest streams of human condition, connecting it to some other form of being. Music also happens over time, and music happens because of change. Music encodes our feelings better than any other aid we may have. Toccata incorporates this at its very core, as the main sound is Andreas' family piano where he learned to play, sampled this past July.

Read more about the piece, and the collaboration between Marcelo and Andreas on andreasrau.eu/toccata

---

Basic controls:
- Click on the piece or press spacebar to start it (WebAudio requires user intervention for the music to start). Once the music has started, again click or press spacebar to play/pause.
- Press “s” to save a still at the current resolution
- Press “r” to start recording a video at the current resolution, then “r” again to stop.

---

WebM audio-video recording performed using the library RecordRTC by https://muazkhan.com/, MIT licence.

metadata.name: Dencity #908
metadata.description:
Dencity is a generative art project inspired by aerial views of cities with a high density of buildings. Its perspective effect, its perfectly imprecise lines, its subtle textures and its very advanced level of detail give it the appearance of a hand-drawn work.

Behind the visible art (the image) hides another form of art, an extremely complex algorithm capable of calculating and drawing in 2D each variation of the Dencity project. To draw a variation, the algorithm notably takes around 3,000,000 to 20,000,000 random decisions based on the hash of the mint and draws around 800,000 to 4,000,000 lines to create all the strokes and texture effects.

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.

metadata.name: Constellations #4
metadata.description:
We look at things that are seemingly random and can't help but form relationships between them. For centuries people of many different nations and cultures have looked up to the skies and perceived patterns, objects, mythical creatures from scattered stars.

This work, initially titled 'Chaos', began as a study for my project 'Gestalt' to explore the idea of working with a foundation of hidden random points and connecting points with curves in interesting ways. Almost by accident I discovered a technique which ended up creating outputs resembling scenes from some otherworldly cosmos. While it produced some visually interesting outputs, they didn't quite fit the direction for 'Gestalt' and only a portion of the algorithm was used. 

The study was recently revisited and further refined to explore something different to 'Gestalt' (yet would nod to it), blur the lines between abstraction and figuration, and lean into the atmospheric moodiness of that once accidental output. 'Constellations' plays with the concept of interconnectivity, the meeting and interacting of hidden elements, and the emergence of patterns and interpretations from chance encounters (or kismet).

---

Released for VerticalCrypto Art invites | LONDON 2022.

---

Controls:
• 'R' reassembles the piece
• 'B' toggles the frame

Note: Some mints may take time to fully render in live mode.

Made in p5js
Created Oct 2022
Artist: @Yazid

metadata.name: Unfolded #176
metadata.description:
A plane is repeatedly folded over itself, choosing creases either at random, or according to some pattern (like a grid). These creases form the boundaries of the individual textured tiles.

Once the folds are complete, they are undone in reverse order, recreating the original plane. With each unfolding, the orientation of each crease (as a mountain or a valley), and each tile (facing up or down) is recorded as a sequence of 1s and 0s. Tiles are colored and textured according to similarities in these binary sequences, giving rise to subtle symmetries and repetitions.

Written in vanilla JS & HTML5 Canvas.

Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0
